org.midica.file

Class Exporter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.midica.file.Exporter
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MidicaPLExporter, MidiExporter

    public abstract class Exporter
extends java.lang.Object

    This class can be extended by exporter classes which write a music file based on a MIDI sequence.

    Derived classes are MidiExporter and MidicaPLExporter.

    • Method Detail

      • createFile

        protected boolean createFile(java.io.File file)
                      throws ExportException

        Checks and creates the file. Checks if the specified file can be created/written or already exists. If it already exists, asks for overwriting or not. If everything is correct, creates the file.

        Parameters:
        file - the file to be written
        Returns:
        true, if the file can be written. Otherwise: false.
        Throws:
        ExportException - if the file is not writable.

      • export

        public abstract ExportResult export(java.io.File file)
                             throws ExportException

        Exports a file.

        Parameters:
        file - Export file based on the loaded midi stream.
        Returns:
        Warnings that occured during the export.
        Throws:
        ExportException - If the file can not be exported correctly.
